						               													<description>Listed in American Games, #4670.  1947, Comics, Board game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The directions to play the game are printed on the underside of the lid. This game is for two, three, or four players and has one die and four character pawns - Gordo, Pepito, Juan Pablo Jones and the Poet. All players start at the space picturing Gordo and Pepito. The object of the game is to move your character pawn along the path of sombreros on the board and be the first to arrive in the space picturing Juan Pablo Jones and the Poet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the player lands on a Black Sombrero, s/he must take a &amp;quot;siesta&amp;quot; and miss a turn.  If all four players end up taking a siesta, they all roll and the highest number rolls again to resume play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
